===Noun===
'''stone''' (''[[countable]] and [[uncountable]]''; ''plural'' '''stones''' ''except as shown below'')

#(''uncountable'') A hard [[earth]]en substance that can form large [[rock]]s and [[boulder]]s.
#A small piece of stone.
#(''UK'') (''plural'' '''stone''') A unit of measurement equal to 14 [[pound]]s, used mainly to measure human weight.
#:''I weigh nine and a half stone.''
#(''medical'') A hard, stone-like [[deposit]] 
#:''kidney stone''
#A piece made of any hard material, used in various [[game]]s such as [[backgammon]]

